longBusinessSummary: Hillcrest Energy Technologies Ltd. engages in the acquisition, exploration, development, and production of oil and gas reserves in North America. The company has an option to acquire 75% working interest in West Hazel field, a petroleum asset located in the Western Canadian Sedimentary Basin, Saskatchewan. It focuses on transitioning its business to the development and deployment of clean energy technology with a focus on electrification and electric machine control technology. The company was formerly known as Hillcrest Petroleum Ltd. and changed its name to Hillcrest Energy Technologies Ltd. in April 2021. Hillcrest Energy Technologies Ltd. was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
